oing%20it.%20But%20he%20is%20not%20here%E2%80%A6%20The%20%E2%80%98villain%E2%80%99%20is%20not%20being%20heard.%20He%20should%20come%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Dhulia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%E2%80%99s%20remarks%20were%20in%20response%20to%20submissions%20made%20by%20%3Cem%3Eamicus%20curiae%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Esenior%20advocate%20Aparajita%20Singh%2C%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20November%2021%2C%20that%20748%20fires%20were%20lit%20across%20stubbled%20paddy%20fields%20in%20Punjab%20on%20Sunday%2C%20November%2019%2C%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Punjab%20government%20says%20it%20is%20doing%20everything.%20But%20it%20is%20not%20visible%20on%20the%20ground%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20pointed%20out%20to%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Sanjay%20Kishan%20Kaul%2C%20who%20is%20heading%20the%20Bench%2C%20struck%20a%20divergent%20note%20to%20that%20of%20his%20fellow%20judge.%20He%20observed%20that%20farmers%20who%20are%20violating%20the%20law%2C%20despite%20court%20orders%20and%20counselling%20against%20stubble-burning%2C%20%E2%80%9Cshould%20feel%20the%20pinch%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDespite%20court%20orders%20and%20counselling%2C%20for%20their%20two%20bit%20of%20money%20and%20no%20matter%20how%20the%20fires%20affect%20the%20environment%20and%20children%2C%20they%20do%20it%E2%80%A6%20Why%20should%20people%20who%20violate%20the%20law%20benefit%20monetarily%3F%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Kaul%20asked%20pointedly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20sought%20to%20know%20from%20the%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20governments%20why%20farmers%20flouting%20orders%20should%20be%20considered%20for%20minimum%20support%20price%20(MSP).%20%E2%80%9CTake%20away%20the%20incentive%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Kaul%20said%20sharply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Dhulia%20chimed%20in%20to%20underline%20that%20MSP%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Csensitive%20issue%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20representative%20of%20everybody%20here%20except%20farmers%E2%80%A6%20Farmers%20must%20be%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Dhulia%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Justice%20Kaul%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20lighting%20fires%20will%20not%20come%20here%20and%20people%20following%20the%20law%20need%20not%20come%20here.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Punjab%20advocate%20general%2C%20Gurminder%20Singh%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%208%2C481%20meetings%20had%20been%20held%20with%20farmers%20across%20the%20state%20and%20that%20the%20government%20pressed%20into%20action%201%2C092%20flying%20squads%20to%20prevent%20stubble%20burning.%20Singh%20also%20added%20that%20so%20far%20980%20FIRs%20had%20been%20registered%20against%20landowners%20who%20violated%20the%20norms%20against%20setting%20fires%2C%20and%20over%20Rs%202%20crore%20had%20been%20estimated%20as%20environmental%20compensation%20due.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Kaul%2C%20at%20this%20stage%20of%20the%20hearing%2C%20rued%20that%20land%20in%20Punjab%20is%20becoming%20arid%20due%20to%20extensive%20cultivation%20of%20paddy.%20%E2%80%9CSomewhere%2C%20farmers%20have%20to%20understand%20the%20fallout%20of%20paddy%20cultivation%E2%80%A6%20Whether%20there%20can%20be%20a%20policy%20by%20which%20you%20%5Bthe%20government%5D%20could%20discourage%20paddy%20and%20encourage%20other%20crops%20in%20Punjab%E2%80%A6%20water%20is%20becoming%20scarce%20and%20the%20wells%20are%20running%20dry%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20had%20earlier%2C%20on%20November%207%2C%20ordered%20the%20state%20governments%20of%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Rajasthan%20to%20ensure%20that%20stubble%20burning%20is%20stopped%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fair-pollution-sc-directs-punjab-haryana-up-and-rajasthan-to-immediately-stop-crop-residue-burning%2Farticle67507586.ece%5C%22%3Eforthwith%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20as%20an%20immediate%20measure%20to%20protect%20the%20lives%20and%20health%20of%20people.%