g%20Niger%2C%20including%20limited%20school%20supplies.%20The%20court%20adjourned%20until%20December%207.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fnigers-junta-asks-west-africas-court-to-compel-neighbours-to-lift-coup-sanctions-citing-hardship%2Farticleshow%2F105394732.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fnigers-junta-asks-west-africas-court-to-compel-neighbours-to-lift-coup-sanctions-citing-hardship%2Famp_articleshow%2F105394732.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fnigers-junta-asks-west-africas-court-to-compel-neighbours-to-lift-coup-sanctions-citing-hardship%2Famp_articleshow%2F105394732.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22North%20Korea%20claims%20its%203rd%20attempt%20to%20put%20a%20spy%20satellite%20into%20orbit%20was%20successful%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700587890000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105394714%2Cimgsize-87994.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fnorth-korea-claims-its-3rd-attempt-to-put-a-spy-satellite-into-orbit-was-successful%2Farticleshow%2F105394720.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105394720.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fnorth-korea-claims-its-3rd-attempt-to-put-a-spy-satellite-into-orbit-was-successful%2Farticleshow%2F105394720.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fnorth-korea-claims-its-3rd-attempt-to-put-a-spy-satellite-into-orbit-was-successful%2Famp_articleshow%2F105394720.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fnorth-korea-claims-its-3rd-attempt-to-put-a-spy-satellite-into-orbit-was-successful%2Famp_articleshow%2F105394720.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Urgent%20Need%20for%20Higher%20Climate%20Action%20to%20Limit%20Global%20Warming%3A%20UNEP%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21221833%2Fella-ivanescu-JbfhNrpQ_dw-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBengaluru%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Global%20temperatures%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2F2023-on-track-to-become-hottest%5C%22%3Ebroken%20records%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year.%20As%20per%20the%20latest%20Emissions%20Gap%20Report%20released%20by%20the%20UN%20Environment%20Programme%20(UNEP)%20on%20November%2020%2C%20the%20current%20pledges%20under%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20put%20the%20world%20on%20track%20for%20a%202.5-2.9%C2%B0C%20temperature%20rise%20above%20pre-industrial%20levels%20this%20century%2C%20far%20higher%20than%20the%20limit%20of%20restricting%20global%20warming%20to%20a%201.5%20or%202%C2%B0C%20temperature%20rise.%20This%20points%20to%20the%20urgent%20need%20for%20increased%20climate%20action%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20released%20less%20than%2010%20days%20ahead%20of%20the%20UN%20climate%20change%20summit%20in%20Dubai%20in%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20shows%20how%20crucial%20discussions%20revolving%20around%20reframing%20new%20Nationally%20Determined%20Contributions%20or%20NDCs%20that%20countries%20should%20commit%20to%20%E2%80%93%20to%20keep%20global%20warming%20to%20below%20subscribed%20levels%20as%20per%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20of%202015%20%E2%80%93%20would%20be%20during%20the%20climate%20conference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20that%20nations%20make%20more%20ambitious%20pledges%2C%20and%20move%20towards%20immediate%20but%20also%20just%20and%20equitable%20climate%20action%2C%20experts%20and%20activists%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERecord%20high%20emissions%20in%202022%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwedocs.unep.org%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F20.500.11822%2F43922%2FEGR2023.pdf%3Fsequence%3D3%26isAllowed%3Dy%5C%22%3EEmissions%20Gap%20Report%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20by%20the%20UNEP%20on%20November%2020%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%9CBroken%20Record%20%E2%80%93%20Temperatures%20hit%20new%20highs%2C%20yet%20world%20fails%20to%20cut%20emissions%20(again)%E2%80%9D%2C%20is%20the%2014th%20of%20its%20kind%20so%20far.%20Emission%20Gap%20Reports%20are%20released%20annually%20by%20the%20UNEP%20and%20provide%20a%20scientific%20assessment%20of%20the%20gap%20between%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20reductions%20pledged%20by%20countries%20and%20the%20reductions%20that%20are%20now%20required%20to%20meet%20the%20goals%20of%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20of%202015.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fmost-requested%2Fkey-aspects-of-the-paris-agreement%23%3A~%3Atext%3DLong%252Dterm%2520temperature%2520goal%2520(Art%2Cthe%2520increase%2520to%25201.5%2520degrees.%5C%22%3EAgreement%3C%2Fa%3E%20necessitates%20that%20signatory%20countries%20reduce%20their%20emissions%20to%20keep%20global%20warming%20limited%20to%20within%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20or%20well%20below%20a%202%20degrees%20Celsius%20scenario.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Emissions%20Gap%20Report%20is%20crucial%20for%20it%20can%20help%20channel%20the%20next%20round%20of%20NDCs%20that%20countries%20should%20commit%20to%2C%20to%20keep%20global%20warming%20to%20below%20subscribed%20levels.%20These%20are%20subjects%20that%20will%20be%20under%20discussion%20at%20the%20upcoming%20UN%20climate%20change%20conference%2C%20COP28%2C%20scheduled%20to%20take%20place%20in%20Dubai%20in%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20between%20November%2030%20and%20December%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%E2%80%99s%20Emissions%20Gap%20Report%20shows%20that%20global%20greenhouse%20gas%20(GHG)%20emissions%20reached%20a%20record%20high%20of%2057.4%20gigatonnes%20worth%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20equivalent%20(GtCO2e)%20in%202022%2C%20which%20is%20an%20increase%20of%201.2%25%20when%20compared%20to%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCO2%20emissions%20from%20fossil%20fuel%20combustion%20and%20industrial%20processes%20were%20the%20main%20contributors%20to%20the%20overall%20increase%2C%20accounting%20for%20about%20two%20thirds%20of%20current%20GHG%20emissions%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20meet%20the%20goals%20of%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%2C%20GHG%20emissions%20must%20decline%20to%20between%2033-41%20GtCO2e%20by%202030%2C%20as%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20the%20top%20seven%20global%20emitters%20in%202022%20remain%20the%20same%20as%20in%202021.%20They%20are%20Brazil%2C%20China%2C%20India%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20the%20Russian%20Federation%20and%20the%20United%20States%20of%20America.%20Together%20(and%20including%20international%20transport)%2C%20these%20emitters%20accounted%20for%20a%20total%20of%2033%20GtCO2e%20in%202021%2C%20or%2065%25%20of%20global%20emissions%20(on%20a%20territorial%20basis).%20Emissions%20of%20the%20G20%20members%20increased%20in%202022%20and%20accounted%20for%20three%20quarters%20of%20the%20total.%20The%20G20%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20which%20also%20includes%20India%20%E2%80%93%20accounted%20for%2076%25%20of%20global%20emissions.%20Low%20and%20middle-income%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20including%20India%2C%20China%2C%20Brazil%20and%20Argentina%2C%20among%20others%20%E2%80%93%20contributed%2053%25%20in%202000%2C%20and%20this%20rose%20to%2069%25%20in%202021.%20Preliminary%20estimates%20of%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20increased%20for%20several%20countries%20in%202022%20when%20compared%20to%202021%2C%20including%20India%20(an%20increase%20of%205.1%25)%20and%20Indonesia%20(10%25)%2C%20while%20it%20decreased%20in%20several%20others%20such%20as%20Brazil%20(a%20decrease%20of%202.5%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20found%20that%20energy%20supply%20was%20the%20largest%20source%20of%20emissions%20at%2020.9%20GtCO2e%20(36%25%20of%20the%20total)%20in%202022.%20This%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20is%20mainly%20caused%20by%20combustion%20emissions%20in%20the%20power%20sector%20(14.8%20GtCO2e)%20and%20emissions%20from%20fossil%20fuel%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInequality%20in%20consumption-based%20emissions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20a%20lot%20of%20inequality%20in%20consumption-based%20emissions%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%20Per%20capita%20territorial%20GHG%20emissions%20vary%20significantly%20across%20countries%3A%20they%20are%20more%20than%20double%20the%20world%20average%20(of%206.5%20tonnes%20of%20CO2e)%20in%20Russia%20and%20the%20US%2C%20while%20India%E2%80%99s%20is%20less%20than%20half%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGlobally%2C%20the%2010%25%20of%20the%20population%20with%20the%20highest%20income%20accounted%20for%20nearly%20half%20(48%25)%20of%20emissions%20with%20two-thirds%20of%20this%20group%20living%20in%20developed%20countries.%20The%20bottom%2050%25%20of%20the%20world%20population%20contributed%20only%2012%25%20of%20total%20emissions%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20historic%20emissions%20and%20their%20contributions%20to%20global%20warming%20also%20varied%20across%20nations.%20It%20noted%20that%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20which%20accounts%20for%20only%204%25%20of%20the%20current%20world%20population%20%E2%80%93%20contributed%20to%2017%25%20of%20global%20warming%20from%201850%20to%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20accounts%20for%2018%25%20of%20the%20world%20population%2C%20but%20to%20date%20only%20contributed%20%5Bto%5D%205%25%20of%20warming%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20current%20policies%20are%20continued%2C%20global%20warming%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20limited%20to%203%C2%B0C%20before%20pre-industrial%20levels%20throughout%20the%20current%20century%20%E2%80%93%20and%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%2066%25%20chance%20of%20this%20happening%2C%20per%20the%20report.%20Delivering%20on%20all%20unconditional%20and%20conditional%20pledges%20by%202030%20lowers%20this%20estimate%20to%202.5%C2%B0C.%20However%2C%20fulfilling%20all%20additional%20net-zero%20pledges%20of%20all%20parties%20will%20bring%20it%20to%202%C2%B0C%2C%20which%20is%20almost%20in%20line%20with%20the%20Paris%20Agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20prospects%20aren%E2%80%99t%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImplementation%20of%20the%20NDCs%20will%20be%20key.%20The%20world%20will%20need%20to%20cut%20emissions%20by%2028%25%20by%202030%20to%20achieve%20the%202%C2%B0C%20goal%20of%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%2C%20and%20by%2042%25%20to%20achieve%20the%201.5%C2%B0C%20goal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20in%20the%20most%20optimistic%20scenario%20considered%20in%20this%20report%2C%20the%20chance%20of%20limiting%20global%20warming%20to%201.5%C2%B0C%20is%20only%2014%20per%20cent%2C%20and%20the%20various%20scenarios%20leave%20open%20a%20large%20possibility%20that%20global%20warming%20exceeds%202%C2%B0C%20or%20even%203%C2%B0C%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202023%20Emissions%20Gap%20Report%20also%20finds%20that%20energy%20transitions%20will%20be%20crucial%20in%20limiting%20global%20warming%20to%20the%20desired%20limits.%20Delaying%20GHG%20emissions%20reductions%20will%20also%20increase%20our%20reliance%20on%20carbon%20dioxide%20removal%20mechanisms%20from%20the%20atmosphere%20in%20future%2C%20such%20as%20through%20afforestation%2C%20reforestation%20and%20forest%20management.%20The%20Report%20also%20highlighted%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccountries%20with%20greater%20capacity%20and%20greater%20historic%20responsibility%20for%20emissions%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20high-income%20and%20high-emitting%20G20%20countries%20will%20need%20to%20take%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20ambitious%20and%20rapid%20action%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Chilling%20reality%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98on%20thin%20ice%E2%80%99%3A%20Activists%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20Emissions%20Gap%20Report%202023%20%E2%80%9Cpresents%20a%20chilling%20reality%E2%80%9D%2C%20Harjeet%20Singh%2C%20head%20of%20global%20political%20strategy%20at%20Climate%20Action%20Network%20International%2C%20told%20Climate%20Trends%2C%20a%20research-based%20consulting%20and%20capacity%20building%20initiative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20world%20is%20teetering%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20a%20catastrophic%20temperature%20rise%2C%20with%20predictions%20pointing%20towards%20a%202.5-2.9%C2%B0C%20increase%20above%20pre-industrial%20levels%20if%20current%20trends%20continue%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20on%20thin%20ice.%20The%20stark%20reality%20is%20that%20the%20projected%20emissions%20from%20coal%2C%20oil%2C%20and%20gas%20extraction%20are%20on%20track%20to%20exceed%20the%20carbon%20budget%20needed%20to%20limit%20warming%20to%201.5%C2%B0C%20by%20over%203.5%20times.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20window%20for%20action%20is%20rapidly%20closing%2C%20and%20unless%20we%20act%20urgently%20and%20dramatically%20to%20shift%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20and%20embrace%20green%20energy%2C%20the%20chances%20of%20limiting%20warming%20to%20even%201.5%C2%B0C%20are%20dismally%20low%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20vast%20contrast%20between%20our%20current%20trajectory%20and%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20goals%20highlights%20the%20failure%20of%20rich%20countries%20to%20meet%20their%20climate%20commitments%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20have%20not%20only%20fallen%20short%20in%20reducing%20emissions%20but%20also%20in%20providing%20essential%20financial%20support%20to%20nations%20most%20vulnerable%20to%20climate%20impacts.%20This%20represents%20a%20glaring%20gap%20between%20rhetoric%20and%20reality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20world%20needs%20now%20is%20%E2%80%9Ctransformative%20action%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20time%20for%20bold%2C%20decisive%2C%20and%20equitable%20climate%20action%20is%20now%20%E2%80%93%20anything%20less%20is%20a%20betrayal%20to%20current%20and%20future%20generations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImportance%20of%20COP28%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20know%20it%20is%20still%20possible%20to%20make%20the%201.5%20degree%20limit%20a%20reality%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Ant%C3%B2nio%20Guterres%2C%20Secretary-General%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20requires%20tearing%20out%20the%20poisoned%20root%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis%3A%20fossil%20fuels.%20And%20it%20demands%20a%20just%2C%20equitable%20renewables%20transition.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Ftopics%2Fglobal-stocktake%5C%22%3Eglobal%20stocktake%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20which%20involves%20analysing%20aspects%20worldwide%20climate%20action%20and%20support%2C%20identifying%20gaps%2C%20and%20working%20together%20to%20agree%20on%20solutions%20pathways%20%E2%80%93%20will%20conclude%20at%20COP%2028%20in%20Dubai%20this%20year%2C%20and%20this%20will%20inform%20the%20next%20round%20of%20NDCs%20that%20will%20set%20the%20new%20national%20emissions%20targets%20for%202035%2C%20said%20Inger%20Andersen%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20UNEP%2C%20in%20the%202023%20Emissions%20Gap%20Report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAmbition%20in%20these%20NDCs%20must%20bring%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20in%202035%20to%20levels%20consistent%20with%20the%202%C2%B0C%20and%201.5%C2%B0C%20pathways.%20Stronger%20implementation%20in%20this%20decade%20will%20help%20to%20make%20this%20possible.%20The%20world%20needs%20to%20lift%20the%20needle%20out%20of%20the%20groove%20of%20insufficient%20ambition%20and%20action%2C%20and%20start%20setting%20new%20records%20on%20cutting%20emissions%2C%20green%20and%20just%20transitions%2C%20and%20climate%20finance%20%E2%80%93%20starting%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700585515000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21221833%2Fella-ivanescu-JbfhNrpQ_dw-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Furgent-need-for-higher-climate-action-to-limit-global-warming-unep-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20are%20huge%20inequalities%20in%20consumption-based%20emissions%20too%3B%20India%E2%80%99s%20is%20less%20than%20half%20of%20the%20world%20average%2C%20while%20both%20Russia%20and%20the%20US%20consume%20more%20than%20double%20the%20world%20average%2C%20the%202023%20Emissions%20Gap%20Report%20says.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Furgent-need-for-higher-climate-action-to-limit-global-warming-unep-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Video%20shows%20car%20interior%20mauled%20by%20a%20trapped%20bear%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700585108000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F361C%2Fproduction%2F_131725831_p0gv18t6.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-67459289%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Wildlife%20officials%20in%20Colorado%20say%20the%20animal%20likely%20entered%20the%20vehicle%20searching%20for%20food.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fav%2Fworld-us-canada-67459289%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rolling%20Stones%20to%20tour%20North%20America%20off%20back%20of%20new%20album%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%