s%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fnokia-bags-multi-terabit-pan-indian-optical-network-deal-from-bharti-airtel-123112101034_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fnokia-bags-multi-terabit-pan-indian-optical-network-deal-from-bharti-airtel-123112101034_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20Trade%20Unionist%2C%20Parliamentarian%2C%20Basudeb%20Acharia%20Dedicated%20His%20Life%20to%20Working%20Classes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21200929%2FThe-Wire-84.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20demise%20of%20Comrade%20Basudeb%20Acharia%2C%20the%20working%20class%20lost%20one%20of%20the%20finest%20leaders%20who%20dedicated%20his%20life%20towards%20the%20betterment%20of%20the%20working%20class.%20Acharia%20(81)%20breathed%20his%20last%20on%20November%2013.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20many%20bourgeoisie%20trade%20union%20leaders%2C%20he%20never%20used%20trade%20union%20activities%20for%20his%20personal%20gains.%20He%20had%20deep%20sympathy%20for%20the%20suffering%20working%20people%20and%20tried%20his%20best%20to%20reduce%20their%20pain.%20He%20was%20one%20of%20the%20most%20prominent%20leaders%20of%20the%20coal%20mine%20workers%20union%20and%20railway%20workers%20union.%20He%20was%20active%20in%20the%20Raniganj%20Coal%20mine%20and%20Dhanbad%20Coal%20mine%20area%2C%20establishing%20Mazdoor%20Union%20as%20its%20vice%20president.%20He%20also%20served%20as%20the%20president%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Coal%20Workers%20Federation.%20His%20decades-long%20efforts%20brought%20about%20a%20positive%20turnaround%20in%20the%20lives%20of%20coal%20mine%20workers.%C2%A0Alongside%2C%20he%20also%20worked%20towards%20strengthening%20the%20Steel%20Employees%20Union%20and%20also%20contributed%20towards%20mordenising%20Durgapur%20Steel%20Factory%20by%20pursuing%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20helped%20the%20Railway%20Workers%20Union%20and%20led%20them%20in%20many%20struggles%20to%20improve%20their%20fate.%20He%20worked%20hard%20during%20the%20railway%20strikes%20in%201974%20and%20was%20arrested%20and%20jailed%20for%20organising%20the%20strike.%20He%20also%20organised%20insurance%20agent%20contract%20workers%20in%20the%20country.%20His%20contribution%20towards%20building%20the%20Bank%20Employees%20Movement%20is%20remarkable.%20The%20Grameen%20Bank%20employees%20also%20worked%20under%20his%20guidance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20worked%20also%20for%20the%20CESE%20Employees%20Union%20and%20ESTC%20union%20while%20helping%20the%20electricity%20struggle.%C2%A0%20He%20was%20the%20president%20of%20the%20LIC%20Agents%20Union.%20He%20also%20helped%20the%20Calcutta%20Port%20Trust%20Union%2C%20in%20their%20movements.%20He%20also%20helped%20in%20building%20the%20Pearless%20Employees%20Union%20through%20his%20remarkable%20contributions.%20He%20joined%20the%20All%20India%20Reserve%20Bank%20Employees%20Movement%20many%20times.%20Building%20many%20trade%20unions%20and%20leading%20their%20struggle%2C%20he%20became%20an%20important%20leader%20of%20the%20Centre%20of%20Indian%20Trade%20Unions%20(CITU)%20and%20became%20its%20all-India%20vice%20president.%20As%20CITU%20leader%2C%20he%20also%20organised%20the%20workers%20of%20Damodar%20Valley%20Corporation%20under%20DVC%20Shramik%20Union%20and%20contract%20workers%20in%20the%20Railways%2C%20the%20Thermal%20Power%20Station%2C%20Cement%20Industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImmense%20contribution%20as%20a%20parliamentarian%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20had%20he%20worked%20for%20the%20trade%20union%20movement%2C%20but%20his%20contribution%20as%20a%20parliament%20member%20was%20also%20immense%20towards%20the%20cause%20of%20working-class%20people.%C2%A0During%20his%20three%20and%20half%20decades%20of%20work%20as%20an%20MP%2C%20he%20brought%20hundreds%20of%20workers%E2%80%99%20issues%20to%20the%20forefront%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20No%20MP%20had%20raised%20so%20many%20trade%20union%20and%20working-class%20issues%20in%20the%20parliament%2C%20in%20a%20number%20of%20ways.%20Almost%20every%20day%20during%20the%20parliament%20session%2C%20he%20would%20raise%20one%20or%20other%20workers%E2%80%99%20issues.%20He%20contributed%20to%20all%20the%20labour-related%20laws%20brought%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20during%20those%20three%20and%20half%20decades.%20He%20commanded%20the%20respect%20of%20the%20House%20for%20his%20great%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcharia%20and%20I%20began%20working%20as%20MPs%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20which%20continued%20for%20the%20next%20three%20decades.%20His%20dedication%20towards%20the%20parliamentary%20work%20was%20unprecedented.%20During%20that%20period%2C%20there%20was%20not%20a%20single%20issue%20on%20which%20he%20did%20not%20submit%20a%20notice%20to%20the%20speaker%20under%20different%20rules%20and%20zero%20hours.%20He%20was%20almost%20a%20permanent%20member%20of%20the%20Railway%20Standing%20Committee%2C%20and%20served%20as%20the%20chairman%20of%20that%20committee%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20His%20knowledge%20of%20railways%20was%20remarkable%2C%20sometimes%20even%20better%20than%20the%20railway%20ministers.%20His%20speeches%20on%20the%20railway%20budget%2C%20issues%20and%20accidents%2C%20workers%E2%80%99%20and%20employees%E2%80%99%20issues%20would%20be%20the%20single%20largest%20volume%20of%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20brought%20many%20changes%20in%20the%20railways%20through%20his%20recommendation%20as%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20Railway%20Standing%20Committee.%20His%20attendance%20in%20the%20parliament%20was%20at%20its%20highest%2C%20as%20he%20would%20stay%20throughout%20the%20session%2C%20starting%20from%2011%20am%20towards%20the%20end%20of%20every%20day%E2%80%99s%20session.%20He%20used%20every%20opportunity%2C%20under%20different%20parliamentary%20rules%2C%20to%20intervene%20on%20various%20public%20issues%20to%20contribute%20to%20the%20legislative%20debate.%20He%20was%20also%20on%20important%20parliamentary%20committees%20like%20the%20Public%20Undertaking%20Committee%2C%20Committees%20on%20Government%20Assurance%2C%20Committee%20on%20Petition%2C%20Committee%20on%20Agriculture%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20brought%20many%20Private%20Members%E2%80%99%20Bills%20to%20the%20House%2C%20many%20of%20which%20were%20accepted%20by%20the%20governments%20and%20were%20brought%20out%20as%20Bills%20later.%20He%20made%20a%20large%20number%20of%20suggestions%20which%20led%20to%20the%20amendments%20in%20various%20Bills%20throughout%20his%20parliamentary%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20made%20it%20a%20point%20to%20meet%20ministers%20every%20day%20on%20people%E2%80%99s%20issues.%20Sometimes%2C%20he%20also%20led%20delegations%20of%20students%2C%20workers%2C%20peasants%2C%20youth%2C%20women%2C%20among%20others%20to%20meet%20ministers%20concerned%20to%20press%20for%20the%20resolution%20of%20their%20issues.%20While%20other%20MPs%20did%20that%20too%2C%20there%20was%20no%20comparison%20to%20the%20level%20at%20which%20Acharia%20had%20done.%20His%20busy%20schedule%20never%20restricted%20him%20from%20raising%20public%20issues%20with%20ministers.%20His%20official%20residence%20always%20teemed%20with%20people%20from%20all%20walks%20of%20life%20who%20reached%20out%20to%20him%20for%20help.%20Acharia%20ensured%20that%20he%20listened%20to%20each%20of%20them%20patiently.%20While%20he%20was%20firm%20in%20commitment%20towards%20the%20causes%20he%20believed%20in%2C%20he%20was%20soft%20in%20his%20nature%2C%20exuding%20qualifies%20of%20the%20highest%20morality%2C%20integrity%2C%20and%20honesty.%20He%20walked%20the%20talk%20on%20any%20public%20issue%20he%20took%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20being%20a%20trade%20union%20and%20workers%E2%80%99%20leader%2C%20he%20took%20up%20farmers%E2%80%99%20issues%20consistently%20both%20in%20the%20parliament%20and%20outside%2C%20emphasising%20the%20need%20for%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20M.S.%20Swaminathan%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20recommendation%20on%20remunerative%20price.%C2%A0His%20role%20in%20the%20enactment%20of%20the%20pro-farmer%20Land%C2%A0%20Acquisition%20Rehabilitation%20and%20Resettlement%20legislation%20earned%20him%20wide%20respect%20across%20all%20farmers%E2%80%99%20groups.%20He%20stood%20up%20for%20the%20rights%20of%20farmers%20and%20dependants%20on%20land%20by%20moving%20numerous%20amendments%20to%20the%20Bill.%20He%20was%20a%20strong%20voice%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20the%20rights%20of%20agricultural%20labour%20and%20for%20the%20effective%20implementation%20of%20the%20MNREGA%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Acts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20played%20a%20pioneering%20role%20in%20organising%20silk%20farmers%20and%20workers%20and%20took%20up%20their%20issues%20with%20the%20government%20and%20the%20Central%20Silk%20Board.%20On%20the%20problem%20of%20sugarcane%20farmers%20and%20their%20mounting%20arrears%2C%20he%20addressed%20many%20of%20their%20protests.%20As%20a%20chairperson%20of%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Agriculture%2C%20he%20raised%20his%20voice%20against%20corporatisation%20of%20agriculture%2C%20against%20the%20dismantling%20of%20the%20extension%20services%2C%20public%20stockholding%2C%20and%20efforts%20to%20privatise%20the%20Food%20Corporation%20of%20India.%20The%20report%20on%20GM%20crops%20tabled%20during%20his%20tenure%20stressed%20that%20the%20regulatory%20system%20in%20India%20is%20inadequate%2C%20needs%20more%20robust%2C%20ensures%20adequate%20security%20as%20well%20as%20control%20over%20monopolies%20and%20cannot%20ignore%20concerns%20like%20biosafety%20biodiversity%2C%20food%20sovereignty%20and%20farmers%E2%80%99%20livelihood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArcharia%E2%80%99s%20family%20came%20from%20South%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20Tirunelveli.%20His%20forefather%20came%20to%20%E2%80%98Gadi%20Berh%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20Purulia%20district%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20as%20the%20Gadi%20Berh%20Panchakot%20Royal%20family%20brought%20them%20as%20the%20Royal%20priest.%20His%20family%20then%20adopted%20the%20Bengali%20language%20and%20culture.%20Basudeb%E2%80%99s%20wife%20was%20also%20from%20a%20Tamil%20family.%20Basudeb%20was%20born%20on%20July%2011%2C%201942%2C%20in%20Purulia.%20He%20was%20involved%20in%20politics%20during%20his%20student%20life.%20He%20joined%20as%20a%20teacher%20at%20Kashipur%20Panchakot%20Raj%20High%20School.%20Later%20on%2C%20he%20left%20his%20job%20and%20became%20whole%20timer.%20He%20was%20a%20leader%20of%20the%20teachers%E2%80%99%20movement%20in%20the%20Purulia%20district%20and%20state%20level%20and%2C%20a%20leader%20of%20ABTA.%20Then%20he%20was%20involved%20in%20the%20Labour%20movement%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20Coal%20miners%E2%80%99%20organisation%20and%20also%20the%20Railway%20Worker%20Union.%20He%20joined%20CPI(M)%20and%20was%20elected%20to%20the%20Purulia%20District%20Committee%20in%201981%20and%20to%20the%20West%20Bengal%20State%20Committee%20in%201985.%20He%20was%20elected%20to%20the%20Central%20Committee%20of%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%20in%202005%20and%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Control%20Commission%20in%202018.%20He%20remained%20in%20the%20party%20till%20his%20last%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20parliamentary%20career%20was%20long%20and%20glorious.%20He%20was%20elected%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%201980%20from%20Bankura%20and%20re-elected%20a%20total%20of%20nine%20times%20till%202014.%20He%20was%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20CPI%20(M)%20group%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20from%202004%20to%202014.%20He%20played%20an%20important%20role%20as%20the%20chairman%20of%20many%20important%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committees%20as%20stated%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20a%20man%20of%20the%20soil.%20He%20was%20very%20popular%20among%20people%20in%20Purulia%20and%20Bankura.%20His%20place%20of%20work%20was%20Addra-Kashipur%20and%20he%20was%20known%20as%20%E2%80%9CSir%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20district.%20He%20played%20an%20important%20role%20in%20building%20Kashipur%20Maichel%20Madhusudan%20Medical%20College.%20He%20moved%20in%20his%20area%20widely%20on%20a%20motorcycle%20or%20local%20train%2C%20without%20any%20security.%20People%20irrespective%20of%20political%20affiliation%20had%20easy%20access%20to%20him%2C%20and%20he%20never%20discriminated%20any%20anyone.%20He%20always%20looked%20at%20the%20party%20organisation%20in%20his%20district%2C%20took%20political%20classes%2C%20and%20helped%20the%20mass%20organisation%20and%20panchayats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20times%20of%20political%20violence%2C%20he%20stood%20by%20his%20cadres.%C2%A0%20In%20the%202018%20panchayat%20election%2C%20our%20candidates%20could%20not%20submit%20nominations.%20He%20took%20all%20the%20candidates%20and%20went%20to%20submit%20nominations.%20The%20TMC%20workers%20attacked%20him%20and%20he%20was%20badly%20injured%20but%20he%20never%20retreated%20from%20any%20terror.%20He%20was%20always%20a%20source%20of%20courage%20and%20inspiration%20to%20the%20cadres%20and%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20with%20him%20in%20close%20coordination%20for%20more%20than%20four%20decades%20and%20watched%20him%20in%20action.%20In%20parliament%2C%20he%20was%20always%20friendly%2C%20cordial%2C%20and%20gentle%20with%20all%20members%20irrespective%20of%20party%20affiliation%20and%20loved%20by%20all%20including%20the%20staff%20of%20parliament.%20I%20was%20surprised%20by%20his%20energy%20to%20work%20around%20the%20clock.%C2%A0%20He%20did%20justice%20to%20all%20his%20work%20in%20the%20parliament%2C%20in%20his%20constituencies%2C%20in%20hundreds%20of%20trade%20union%20struggles%2C%20attending%20to%20each%20problem%20of%20people%20and%20helping%20them.%20People%20would%20come%20to%20see%20him%20from%20all%20over%20India%20in%20hundreds%2C%20but%20he%20never%20showed%20annoyance%2C%20or%20left%20unattended.%20This%20was%20the%20source%20of%20his%20immense%20popularity.%20He%20lived%20a%20very%20simple%20life%20and%20maintained%20a%20Communist%20standard%20in%20his%20life%20and%20behaviour.%20He%20widely%20travelled%20the%20whole%20country%20to%20attend%20meetings%2C%20conferences%2C%20or%20to%20participate%20in%20struggles%20to%20visit%20if%20people%20were%20attacked%20by%20police%20or%20affected%20by%20communal%20and%20caste%20riots.%20And%20the%20next%20day%20he%20would%20raise%20the%20issue%20in%20parliament.%20Despite%20his%20ill%20health%2C%20he%20never%20shied%20away%20from%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20retirement%20from%20the%20parliament%2C%20he%20was%20fully%20engaged%20in%20organisational%20activities%20of%20the%20party%2C%20trade%20union%20or%20social%20work.%20He%20would%20read%20Marxist%20literature%20and%20party%20literature%20regularly%20to%20keep%20himself%20updated%20and%20inspired.%20His%20family%20has%20been%20living%20in%20Hyderabad%20for%20the%20last%20few%20years.%20Recently%20he%20was%20very%20ill%20due%20to%20age-related%20diseases%20and%20was%20admitted%20to%20a%20private%20hospital.%20But%20finally%2C%20he%20passed%20away%20on%20November%2013%20at%20the%20age%20of%2081%20years.%20A%20few%20months%20back%20his%20wife%20had%20also%20passed%20away.%20He%20left%20behind%20his%20one%20son%20and%20two%20daughters%20and%20lakhs%20of%20comrades%2C%20friends%2C%20sympathizers%20and%20followers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHannan%20Mollah%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20CPI%20(M)%20politburo%2C%20and%20was%20also%20elected%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20eight%20times.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700579428000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21200929%2FThe-Wire-84.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fas-trade-unionist-parliamentarian-basudeb-acharia-dedicated-his-life-to-working-classes%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Acharia%2C%20who%20was%20a%20nine-time%20MP%20from%20West%20Bengal's%20Bankura%20and%20the%20man%20behind%20several%20workers'%20movements%2C%20passed%20away%20on%20November%2013%20at%20the