ary%20Joint%20Meeting%20on%20the%20Middle%20East%20situation%E2%80%9D%20on%20Tuesday%20(November%2021)%2C%20called%20by%20current%20chair%20of%20the%20grouping%20South%20Africa%2C%20has%20served%20to%20highlight%20the%20difference%20in%20opinion%20between%20India%20and%20other%20BRICS-plus%20members%20on%20the%20current%20situation%20in%20Israel-Palestine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20African%20President%20Cyril%20Ramaphosa%2C%20in%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thepresidency.gov.za%2Fspeeches%2Fopening-remarks-president-cyril-ramaphosa-extraordinary-joint-meeting-brics-leaders-and-leaders-invited-brics-members-situation-middle-east%5C%22%3Eopening%20remarks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20used%20strong%20words%20to%20call%20for%20an%20immediate%20ceasefire%20and%20described%20the%20situation%20in%20Gaza%20as%20a%20genocide.%20He%20also%20held%20Israel%20responsible%20for%20committing%20war%20crimes.%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20too%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.news.cn%2F20231121%2F354737dbbf434952a21914b8c215d57f%2Fc.html%5C%22%3Emade%20similar%20remarks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20speaking%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccollective%20punishment%20of%20people%20in%20Gaza%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20need%20for%20a%20ceasefire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20represented%20by%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%2C%20reiterated%20the%20need%20to%20send%20urgent%20humanitarian%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Ramaphosa%20started%20his%20speech%20with%20a%20reference%20to%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20October%207%20attack%20in%20Israeli%20that%20killed%20more%20than%201%2C200%20people%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20address%20focused%20on%20the%20ongoing%20devastation%20in%20Gaza%2C%20where%20over%2011%2C000%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20by%20Israeli%20forces%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%2C%20Ramaphosa%20said%2C%20have%20violated%20international%20law%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20actions%20by%20Israel%20are%20in%20clear%20violation%20of%20international%20law%2C%20including%20the%20UN%20Charter%20and%20the%20Geneva%20Convention%20read%20together%20with%20its%20protocols.%20In%20its%20attacks%20on%20civilians%20and%20by%20taking%20hostages%2C%20Hamas%20has%20also%20violated%20international%20law%20and%20must%20be%20held%20accountable%20for%20these%20actions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20strong%20words%2C%20he%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20collective%20punishment%20of%20Palestinian%20civilians%20through%20the%20unlawful%20use%20of%20force%20by%20Israel%20is%20a%20war%20crime.%20The%20deliberate%20denial%20of%20medicine%2C%20fuel%2C%20food%20and%20water%20to%20the%20residents%20of%20Gaza%20is%20tantamount%20to%20genocide.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20South%20African%20president%20also%20situated%20the%20current%20situation%20in%20the%20history%20of%20occupation%20of%20Palestine.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20atrocities%20that%20we%20have%20witnessed%20are%20the%20latest%20chapter%20in%20a%20painful%20history%20of%20suffering%2C%20oppression%2C%20occupation%20and%20conflict%20going%20back%20more%20than%2075%20years.%20The%20root%20cause%20of%20this%20conflict%20is%20the%20illegal%20occupation%20of%20Palestinian%20territory%20by%20Israel%20as%20reflected%20in%20UN%20Security%20Council%20Resolution%202334%2C%20which%20states%20that%20%E2%80%9CIsraeli%20settlements%20constitutes%20a%20flagrant%20violation%20under%20international%20law.%E2%80%9D%20We%20therefore%20urge%20the%20international%20community%20to%20agree%20on%20urgent%20and%20concrete%20actions%20to%20end%20the%20suffering%20in%20Gaza%20and%20establish%20a%20path%20towards%20a%20just%20and%20peaceful%20resolution%20of%20this%20conflict%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERamaphosa%20demanded%20an%20immediate%20ceasefire%2C%20the%20opening%20of%20humanitarian%20corridors%2C%20the%20release%20of%20civilian%20hostages%2C%20a%20comprehensive%20dialogue%20owned%20by%20Palestinians%20and%20Israelis%2C%20and%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20prosecutions%20on%20war%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20reiterated%20India%E2%80%99s%20longstanding%20policy%20that%20Palestinian%20concerns%20must%20be%20addressed%20and%20that%20a%20two-state%20solution%20is%20the%20answer%20to%20the%20difficulties%20in%20the%20region.%20However%2C%20even%20while%20speaking%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cimmense%20human%20suffering%E2%80%9D%20in%20Gaza%2C%20he%20followed%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20regime%E2%80%99s%20decision%20not%20to%20hold%20Israel%20responsible%20for%20any%20deaths%20over%20the%20last%20five%20weeks%20and%20only%20spoke%20of%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20killings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20ongoing%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict%20in%20Gaza%20is%20causing%20immense%20human%20suffering%2C%20including%20to%20civilians%2C%20elderly%2C%20women%20and%20children.We%20welcome%20all%20efforts%20of%20the%20international%20community%20towards%20de-escalation.%20Right%20now%2C%20there%20is%20an%20urgent%20need%20to%20ensure%20that%20humanitarian%20aid%20and%20relief%20effectively%20and%20safely%20reach%20the%20population%20of%20Gaza.%20It%20is%20also%20imperative%20that%20all%20hostages%20are%20released.%20We%20believe%20that%20there%20is%20a%20universal%20obligation%20to%20observe%20international%20humanitarian%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2FSpeeches-Statements.htm%3Fdtl%2F37280%2FRemarks_by_EAM_Dr_S_Jaishankar_at_the_extraordinary_joint_meeting_of_BRICS%5C%22%3EJaishankar%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20condemning%20the%20attack%20by%20Hamas%2C%20Jaishankar%20did%20not%20name%20the%20Israeli%20state%20when%20talking%20about%20the%20subsequent%20crisis%20and%20civilian%20deaths.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20all%20aware%20that%20the%20immediate%20crisis%20was%20triggered%20by%20the%20terrorist%20attack%20of%207th%20October.%20Where%20terrorism%20itself%20is%20concerned%2C%20none%20of%20us%20should%20or%20can%20compromise%20with%20it.%20Hostage%20taking%20is%20equally%20unacceptable%20and%20cannot%20be%20condoned.%20Subsequent%20developments%20have%20deepened%20our%20concern%20even%20more%20as%20we%20witness%20large%20scale%20civilian%20casualties%20and%20a%20humanitarian%20crisis.%20We%20strongly%20condemn%20any%20death%20of%20civilians%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20position%20on%20Palestine%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20believe%20that%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20must%20be%20addressed%20in%20a%20serious%20and%20sustainable%20manner.%20This%20can%20only%20happen%20with%20a%20two-State%20solution%20that%20is%20based%20on%20peaceful%20co-existence.%20We%20have%20been%20consistently%20supportive%20of%20international%20efforts%20towards%20this%20end.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20also%20mentioned%20the%20humanitarian%20relief%20India%20has%20already%20sent%20to%20Gaza%2C%20and%20said%20that%20such%20efforts%20will%20continue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20did%20not%20attend%20the%20BRICS%20meeting%20as%20he%20is%20currently%20campaigning%20for%20the%20upcoming%20assembly%20elections%20in%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20BRICS%20members%2C%20both%20old%20and%20new%2C%20India%20and%20Ethiopia%20were%20the%20only%20two%20to%20abstain%20in%20the%20voting%20for%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20Resolution%20that%20called%20for%20humanitarian%20pause%20to%20allow%20for%20supply%20of%20food%2C%20fuel%20and%20water%20to%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%20All%20the%20other%20members%20had%20voted%20in%20favour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%207%2C%20Hamas%20launched%20a%20terror%20attack%20from%20Gaza%20strip%20into%20southern%20Israel%20and%20killed%20more%20than%201%2C400%20people.%20Since%20then%2C%20Israel%20launched%20counter-strikes%20into%20Gaza%20which%20has%20left%20more%20than%2014%2C000%20people%20dead%2C%20as%20per%20last%20official%20count.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700577631000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21200736%2FScreenshot-2023-11-21-at-8.06.55-PM.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fbrics-meeting-israel-hamas-gaza%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%2C%20represented%20by%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%2C%20reiterated%20the%20need%20to%20send%20urgent%20humanitarian%20aid%20but%20did%20not%20speak%20of%20the%20actions%20of%20the%20Israeli%20state.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fbrics-meeting-israel-hamas-gaza%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bihar%20Caste%20Survey%3A%20The%20Who%E2%80%99s%20Who%20in%20the%20Data%20%7C%20Kamar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21194007%2FWorker-Representative-Flickr.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBeyond%20politics%2C%20the%20Bihar%20caste%20survey%20is%20a%20revolutionary%20document.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20public%20document%2C%20the%20first%20ever%20after%201931%2C%20allowing%20for%20people%20to%20stand%20up%20and%20be%20counted.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20go%20down%20to%20the%20wire%2C%20on%20what%20each%20of%20the%20numbers%20unveiled%20mean.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWho%20are%20the%20people%20referred%20to%20by%20percentages%20in%20the%20survey%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EToday%20we%20look%20at%20Kamar%20(8%2C21%2C103%20people)%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWho%20assigned%20names%20to%20castes%3F%20The%20one%20who%20created%20them%20is%20perhaps%20the%20only%20one%20who%20can%20answer%20this%20question.%20There%20are%20many%20castes%20whose%20names%20make%20their%20status%20or%20occupation%20self-evident.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20term%20Brahmin%20evokes%20a%20sense%20of%20honour.%20Similarly%2C%20Kayastha%20also%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20special%20word.%20Bhumihar%20is%20another%20such%20name%20which%20is%20a%20combination%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Ebhoomi%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(land)%20with%20the%20suffix%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Ehar%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20making%20it%20obvious%20that%20the%20members%20of%20this%20caste%20are%20involved%20in%20agriculture.%20Another%20caste%20is%20Rajput%2C%20which%20must%20include%20those%20who%20belong%20to%20the%20ruling%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20327px)%2085vw%2C%20327px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22327%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%20838w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-210x300.jpg%20210w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-715x1024.jpg%20715w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682410%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22468%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20also%20a%20symbol%20of%20social%20prestige.%20Since%20the%20above-mentioned%20four%20names%20are%20upper%20castes%2C%20their%20names%20are%20indicative%20of%20prestige.%20As%20far%20as%20the%20remaining%20castes%20are%20concerned%2C%20there%20is%20no%20such%20caste%20whose%20name%20evokes%20respect.%20Koeris%20have%20now%20started%20calling%20themselves%20Kushwaha%20after%20the%20name%20of%20Kush%2C%20son%20of%20Ram.%20The%20people%20of%20the%20Bhar%20caste%20have%20also%20started%20identifying%20themselves%20as%20Rajbhar.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20people%20of%20the%20Ramani%2FKahar%20caste%20now%20refer%20to%20their%20caste%20as%20Chandravanshi%20while%20the%20people%20of%20the%20Chamar%20caste%20call%20themselves%20Ravidas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20one%20in%20the%20world%20who%20does%20not%20crave%20for%20a%20respectable%20place%20in%20society.%20But%20this%20hunger%20for%20respect%20has%20deeper%20implications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20caste%20in%20Bihar%20called%20Kamar.%20Though%20Chamar%20and%20Kamar%20differ%20in%20the%20first%20syllable%20in%20their%20names%2C%20they%20have%20innumerable%20similarities.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20Chamar%20caste%20is%20a%20craftsman%20caste%20that%20makes%20all%20kinds%20of%20items%20from%20the%20skin%20of%20dead%20animals%20%E2%80%93%20from%20the%20king%E2%80%99s%20armour%20to%20his%20shoes.%20All%20sound%20amplifying%20instruments%20have%20been%20made%20by%20the%20people%20of%20Chamar%20caste.%20But%20the%20Kamar%20people%20do%20not%20lag%20behind.%20They%20have%20offered%20many%20gifts%20to%20human%20civilisation%20through%20their%20craftsmanship.%20If%20you%20have%20ever%20lived%20in%20a%20village%2C%20any%20object%20you%20see%20made%20of%20wood%20or%20iron%20is%20owing%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20Kamar%20is%20both%20a%20carpenter%20and%20a%20blacksmith.%20In%20fact%2C%20Kamar%20is%20a%20group%20that%20includes%20three%20communities%20%E2%80%93%20blacksmiths%2C%20carpenters%20and%20%3Cem%3Ekarmakar%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Here%2C%20%3Cem%3Ekarmakar%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20a%20completely%20new%20word%20and%20there%20are%20political%20and%20social%20reasons%20behind%20it.%20But%20before%20we%20explain%20this%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20note%20that%20even%20today%20human%20life%20cannot%20be%20imagined%20without%20the%20contribution%20of%20this%20caste.%20Whether%20it%20is%20a%20bed%20to%20sleep%20in%2C%20a%20cot%2C%20a%20stool%20or%20items%20in%20the%20kitchen%2C%20or%20even%20the%20bier%20on%20which%20a%20deceased%20person%E2%80%99s%20body%20is%20placed%20and%20carried%20to%20the%20cremation%20ground%2C%20all%20of%20this%20is%20made%20by%20these%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20is%20that%20two%20things%20have%20been%20done%20with%20the%20creation%20of%20castes.%20Firstly%2C%20the%20people%20of%20upper%20castes%20reserved%20respect%20for%20themselves%2C%20and%20secondly%2C%20the%20labour%20of%20the%20lower%20castes%20was%20devalued.%20They%20were%20told%20what%20their%20job%20was%20and%20that%20they%20did%20not%20deserve%20respect.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20one%20who%20provided%20clean%20clothes%20to%20the%20society%20was%20insulted%20by%20being%20called%20a%20%3Cem%3Edhobi%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%20those%20who%20reared%20cows%20and%20buffaloes%20were%20called%20Gwala%20or%20Gowar%3B%20those%20who%20worked%20in%20leather%20were%20called%20Chamars%20and%20those%20who%20worked%20with%20iron%20and%20wood%20were%20called%20Kamars.%20And%20thus%2C%20their%20hard%20work%20was%20ridiculed%20and%20devalued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20basically%20the%20caste%20system%20is%20founded%20upon%20the%20principles%20of%20denial%20of%20unity%20and%20devaluation%20of%20labour.%20But%20this%20was%20prior%20to%201990%20%E2%80%93%20a%20year%20which%20was%20indeed%20remarkable%20for%20all%20the%20artisan%20and%20farming%20communities%20of%20India.%20It%20was%20during%20this%20year%20that%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20Mandal%20Commission%20came%20into%20effect.%20One%20of%20its%20results%20was%20that%20a%20provision%20of%2027%25%20reservation%20was%20made%20for%20backward%20castes%20in%20government%20jobs.%20But%20its%20social%20impact%20was%20very%20deep.%20With%20this%20single%20step%20a%20social%20revolution%20erupted%20in%20India%2C%20which%20changed%20the%20etymology%20with%20Kamar%20being%20called%20Karmakar%20and%20Chamar%20being%20called%20Charmkar.%20But%20it%20is%20no%20less%20than%20a%20conspiracy%20that%20the%20government%20is%20giving%20credit%20for%20their%20labour%20and%20skill%20to%20the%20Hindu%20god%20Vishwakarma%2C%20even%20though%20their%20skill%20and%20hard%20work%20are%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EActually%2C%20the%20political%20conspiracy%20behind%20dividing%20the%20people%20of%20Kamar%20caste%20into%20carpenters%2C%20blacksmiths%20and%20Kamar%20is%20that%20the%20ruling%20class%20does%20not%20want%20to%20see%20these%20people%20united.%20The%20most%20recent%20and%20official%20evidence%20is%20the%20Caste%20Based%20Enumeration%20Report-2022%20released%20by%20the%20Bihar%20government%2C%20which%20says%20that%20the%20population%20of%20Kamar%20(lohar%20and%20Karmakar)%20is%208%2C21%2C103.%20The%20report%20also%20states%20that%20the%20population%20of%20the%20Badhai%20(carpenter)%20caste%20is%2018%2C95%2C672.%20Now%20if%20we%20add%20these%20two%20figures%2C%20the%20total%20population%20of%20these%20people%20in%20Bihar%20is%2027%2C16%2C775.%20This%20number%20is%20more%20than%20three%20times%20the%20total%20number%20of%20Kayasthas%20in%20Bihar%2C%20which%20is%207%2C85%2C771.%20But%20their%20participation%20in%20governance%20is%20absolutely%20nil.%20In%20the%20name%20of%20resources%2C%20they%20have%20only%20hammers%2C%20chisels%2C%20augers%2C%20trowels%20and%20saws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bihar%20government%20has%20included%20these%20people%20in%20the%20category%20of%20extremely%20backward%20classes.%20But%20is%20that%20what%20these%20people%20deserve%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslated%20from%20Hindi%20by%20Naushin%20Rehman.%20Read%20the%20Hindi%20original%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F260832%2Fbihar-caste-survey-kamaar-caste-society%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20earlier%20parts%20of%20the%20series%20on%20the%20following%20communities%20by%20clicking%20on%20their%20names%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-ghasi%5C%22%3EGhasi%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3ESantrash%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20hre