1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Hurdles%20in%20the%20Way%20of%20Reforming%20Agricultural%20Markets%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F11%2F06091355%2FIMG-20201105-WA0099.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202021%2C%20the%20parliament%20repealed%20the%20three%20farm%20laws%20enacted%20in%202020%3A%20the%20Farmers%20(Empowerment%20and%20Protection)%20Agreement%20on%20Price%20Assurance%20and%20Farm%20Services%20Act%3B%20the%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Produce%20Trade%20and%20Commerce%20(Promotion%20and%20Facilitation)%20Act%3B%20and%20the%20Essential%20Commodities%20(Amendment)%20Act.%20Misinformation%20about%20these%20laws%20persists%2C%20and%20their%20repeal%20is%20cited%20as%20the%20reason%20for%20inflation%2C%20shortages%2C%20and%20other%20multiple%20problems%20plaguing%20Indian%20agriculture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20402px)%2085vw%2C%20402px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21152639%2F9789354424656.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22402%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21152639%2F9789354424656.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21152639%2F9789354424656-205x300.jpg%20205w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685705%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22589%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESukhpal%20Singh%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3ERegulating%20Agricultural%20Markets%20in%20India%3A%20A%20Smallholder%20Perspective%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EOrient%20BlackSwan%20(October%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20book%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3ERegulating%20Agricultural%20Markets%20in%20India%3A%20A%20Smallholder%20Perspective%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20provides%20a%20perspective%20on%20the%20enactment%20and%20later%20the%20repeal%20of%20the%20first%20two%20laws.%20Its%20author%2C%20Sukhpal%20Singh%2C%20is%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Management%2C%20Ahmedabad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20is%20a%20collection%20of%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20articles%20published%20earlier%20in%20various%20reputed%20publications.%20This%20slim%20volume%20has%20only%20six%20chapters%2C%20of%20which%20two%20are%20devoted%20to%20contract%20farming%20and%20its%20regulatory%20framework.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20chapter%20in%20the%20book%20is%20about%20the%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Produce%20Trade%20and%20Commerce%20(Promotion%20and%20Facilitation)%20Act%2C%20which%20was%20basically%20aimed%20at%20bypassing%20the%20agricultural%20produce%20market%20committees%20(APMCs)%20and%20permitting%20trade%20in%20agricultural%20produce%20outside%20their%20physical%20boundaries.%20This%20law%20was%20the%20main%20reason%20for%20the%2014-month-long%20farmers%E2%80%99%20agitation%20on%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20borders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20introductory%20chapter%20highlights%20the%20importance%20of%20small%20and%20marginal%20farmers%20in%20the%20agricultural%20landscape%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018-19%2C%20this%20class%20of%20farmers%20cultivated%20only%2056%25%20of%20the%20area%20but%20accounted%20for%2089%25%20of%20all%20operational%20holdings.%20Even%20though%20the%20official%20statistics%20%E2%80%93%20according%20to%20the%2077%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%20round%20of%20the%20National%20Statistical%20Organisation%E2%80%99s%20Situation%20Assessment%20of%20Agricultural%20Household%20and%20Land%20and%20Livestock%20Holdings%20of%20Households%20in%20Rural%20India%20%E2%80%93%20show%20that%20only%2013%25%20of%20the%20area%20is%20leased%2C%20it%20is%20common%20knowledge%20that%20the%20actual%20incidence%20of%20leasing%20is%20much%20higher.%20The%20chapter%20also%20discusses%20some%20other%20findings%20of%20the%20survey%20including%20the%20trend%20of%20declining%20share%20of%20farmers%E2%80%99%20income%20from%20cultivation%20of%20crops.%20An%20average%20farmer%20now%20earns%20more%20from%20wage%2C%20salary%2C%20and%20income%20from%20animal%20husbandry%20and%20dairying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20disputed%20of%20the%20three%20farm%20laws%20was%20the%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Produce%20Trade%20and%20Commerce%20(Promotion%20and%20Facilitation)%20Act%2C%202020.%20The%20author%20has%20been%20following%20the%20marketing%20laws%20of%20agricultural%20produce%20for%20decades.%20Very%20few%20people%20have%20a%20deeper%20understanding%20of%20laws%20enacted%20by%20the%20state%20governments%20for%20regulating%20the%20wholesale%20trade%20of%20produce%2C%20which%20is%20the%20first%20point%20of%20sale%20of%20farmers%E2%80%99%20produce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20history%20of%20reform%20of%20agricultural%20marketing%20in%20the%20states%20is%20discussed%20in%20detail.%20The%20Union%20government%20had%20circulated%20a%20model%20act%20in%202003.%20It%20was%20titled%20%E2%80%98State%20Agricultural%20Produce%20Marketing%20(Development%20and%20Regulation)%20Act%2C%202003%E2%80%99.%20The%20Union%20government%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20persuade%20the%20states%20to%20adopt%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20model%20Act%20in%20their%20own%20APMC%20Acts.%20The%20model%20Act%20sought%20to%20regulate%20not%20only%20the%20marketing%20of%20produce%20but%20also%20contract%20farming%20operations.%20It%20is%20obvious%20that%20encouragement%20provided%20to%20contract%20farming%20is%20not%20a%20new%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fagriculture-marketing-reforms-federalism%5C%22%3ECentre%E2%80%99s%20Agricultural%20Marketing%20Reforms%20Are%20an%20Assault%20on%20Federalism%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20provisions%20in%20the%20model%20Act%20of%202003%20were%20analysed%20in%20detail%20in%20a%20study%20published%20in%202006%20by%20Consumer%20Unity%20and%20Trust%20Society%20(CUTS)%2C%20Jaipur.%20One%20of%20the%20recommendations%20of%20CUTS%20quoted%20in%20the%20book%20relates%20to%20freeing%20up%20agricultural%20marketing%20by%20allowing%20private%20markets%20to%20compete%20with%20APMCs%20and%20giving%20freedom%20to%20farmers%20to%20sell%20their%20produce%20to%20anybody%20and%20at%20any%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20what%20the%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Produce%20Trade%20and%20Commerce%20(Promotion%20and%20Facilitation)%20Act%2C%202020%20sought%20to%20achieve%20and%20failed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20amendments%20approved%20by%20state%20legislatures%20of%20opposition-ruled%20states%2C%20including%20Punjab%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20and%20Chhatisgarh%2C%20have%20been%20discussed%20in%20the%20book.%20The%20shortcomings%20of%20these%20amendments%20make%20it%20an%20interesting%20read.%20In%20any%20case%2C%20the%20governors%20did%20not%20give%20their%20consent%20to%20the%20state%20amendments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20progress%20of%20the%20e-National%20Agriculture%20Market%20started%20in%202015%20is%20also%20discussed%20in%20the%20book.%20In%20recent%20months%2C%20concerted%20efforts%20have%20been%20made%20to%20make%20it%20mainstream%20for%20inter-state%20trade%2C%20but%20there%20are%20several%20gaps%20in%20the%20regulatory%20regime.%20However%2C%20these%20have%20not%20been%20discussed%20in%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EContract%20farming%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20enriching%20chapter%20of%20the%20book%20is%20on%20legislation%20to%20promote%20and%20regulate%20contract%20farming.%20The%20author%20has%20studied%20this%20subject%20for%20years%20and%20highlights%20that%20despite%20regulatory%20weaknesses%2C%20contract%20farming%20is%20practiced%20in%20several%20parts%20of%20India%20for%20various%20crops.%20A%20table%20giving%20the%20crops%20and%20the%20contracts%20signed%20between%20corporates%20and%20farmers%20is%20enlightening.%20However%2C%20the%20author%20argues%20strongly%20against%20linking%20the%20minimum%20support%20price%20(MSP)%20to%20the%20contracted%20price.%20Similarly%2C%20linking%20the%20contracted%20price%20to%20prices%20in%20APMCs%20goes%20against%20the%20very%20idea%20of%20a%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20chapter%20must%20be%20read%20by%20those%20who%20think%20that%20contract%20farming%20is%20the%20solution%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20agriculture%20and%20rue%20the%20repeal%20of%20the%20Farmers%20(Empowerment%20and%20Protection)%20Agreement%20on%20Price%20Assurance%20and%20Farm%20Services%20Act%2C%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20readers%20of%20this%20review%20will%20easily%20appreciate%20the%20difficulty%20of%20entering%20a%20contract%20with%20a%20much%20more%20powerful%20entity.%20Those%20buying%20flats%20or%20houses%20from%20builders%20know%20what%20exactly%20the%20import%20of%20a%20contract%20between%20unequal%20parties%20is.%20And%20farmers%20are%20much%20weaker%20vis-a-vis%20corporate%20than%20buyers%20of%20flats%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20builders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chapter%20on%20the%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Produce%20Trade%20and%20Commerce%20(Promotion%20and%20Facilitation)%20Act%20provides%20the%20arguments%20advanced%20in%20the%202018%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nipfp.org.in%2Fmedia%2Fmedialibrary%2F2019%2F12%2FEnglish_Annual_Report_NIPFP_18-19.pdf%5C%22%3Eworking%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Public%20Finance%20and%20Policy%20(NIPFP)%2C%20which%20may%20have%20persuaded%20the%20government%20that%20the%20two%20laws%20relating%20to%20APMCs%20and%20contract%20farming%20will%20be%20within%20the%20constitutional%20scheme%20of%20distribution%20of%20powers%20between%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20states.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bqprime.com%2Fpolitics%2Fstates-should-reframe-agri-laws-after-allaying-farmer-concerns-niti-aayogs-ramesh-chand%5C%22%3Edefence%20of%20the%20farm%20laws%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Ramesh%20Chand%2C%20a%20member%20of%20Niti%20Ayog%2C%20is%20also%20discussed%20in%20this%20chapter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20discussion%20in%20the%20book%20about%20the%20law%20which%20has%20been%20regularly%20used%20by%20the%20Union%20and%20state%20governments%20since%20the%20promulgation%20of%20the%20Essential%20Commodities%20(Amendment)%20Ordinance%2C%20on%20June%205%2C%202020.%20The%20Ordinance%2C%20and%20the%20Amendment%20Act%20later%2C%20provided%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20may%20regulate%20the%20supply%20of%20certain%20food%20items%2C%20including%20cereals%2C%20pulses%2C%20potatoes%2C%20onions%2C%20edible%20oilseeds%2C%20and%20oils%2C%20under%20extraordinary%20circumstances%20only.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20EC%20Act%20was%20to%20be%20used%20in%20case%20of%20famine%2C%20war%2C%20grave%20natural%20calamities%2C%20and%20high%20inflation%20leading%20to%20price%20rise.%20The%20amendments%20provided%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20could%20impose%20stock%20limits%20only%20if%20there%20is%20a%20100%25%20increase%20in%20the%20retail%20price%20of%20horticultural%20produce%20and%20a%2050%25%20increase%20in%20the%20retail%20price%20of%20non-perishable%20agricultural%20food%20items.%20The%20increase%20was%20to%20be%20calculated%20over%20the%20retail%20prices%20prevailing%20in%20the%20previous%2012%20months%2C%20or%20the%20average%20retail%20price%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20whichever%20was%20lower.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20amendment%20of%20the%20EC%20Act%20was%20not%20repealed%2C%20the%20government%20would%20not%20have%20been%20able%20to%20use%20it%20as%20an%20important%20instrument%20for%20controlling%20inflation.%20So%2C%20the%20stock%20limit%20on%20wheat%2C%20rice%2C%20pulses%2C%20or%20onions%20would%20not%20have%20been%20possible%20in%20most%20cases%20as%20the%20conditions%20of%20the%20amendment%20were%20not%20met.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chapter%20on%20MSP%20highlights%20the%20difficulties%20in%20making%20it%20a%20legal%20right.%20The%20APMC%20Act%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20has%20a%20provision%20since%201986%20that%20farmers%E2%80%99%20produce%20will%20not%20be%20bought%20below%20MSP%20declared%20by%20the%20state%20government.%20But%20the%20state%20has%20never%20declared%20its%20own%20MSP%20for%20any%20crop!%20So%2C%20the%20provision%20remains%20on%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20a%20large%20and%20agriculturally%20diverse%20nation.%20That%20is%20why%20the%20framers%20of%20the%20constitution%20made%20agriculture%20a%20state%20subject.%20The%20APMC%20laws%20of%20each%20state%20deserve%20detailed%20examination%20and%20analysis.%20This%20slim%20volume%20highlights%20the%20need%20for%20such%20a%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20can%20only%20hope%20that%20academic%20and%20research%20institutions%20will%20be%20provided%20funding%20by%20state%20governments%20and%20the%20Union%20ministry%20of%20agriculture%20for%20such%20studies.%20I%20also%20hope%20that%20agriculture%20ministers%20and%20secretaries%20of%20the%20states%20can%20find%20time%20to%20read%20this%20important%20book%20on%20burning%20issues%20of%20farm%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESiraj%20Hussain%20is%20a%20former%20secretary%20(agriculture)%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700564527000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F11%2F06091355%2FIMG-20201105-WA0099.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fthe-hurdles-in-the-way-of-reforming-agricultural-markets-in-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sukhpal%20Singh's%20latest%20book%20'Regulating%20Agricultural%20Markets%20in%20India%3A%20A%20Smallholder%20Perspective'%20looks%20at%20the%20three%20farm%20laws%20that%20were%20repealed%20following%20criticism%20against%20proposed%20reforms%20to%20the%20system%20of%20agricultural%20markets%2C%20among%20other%20things.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fthe-hurdles-in-the-way-of-reforming-agricultural-markets-in-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%